==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*gunða-'', from Indo-European ''*gʷhen-'' ‘hit, drive’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[gudea|gūdea]], Old High German ''gund-'' (in [[gundfano]] ‘war-flag’), Old Norse [[guðr]], [[gunnr]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[defendere]], Slavic ''*gъnati-'' (Old Church Slavonic [[гънати]], Russian [[гнать]]), Baltic ''*giñ-'' (Lithuanian [[giñti]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /gu:θ/

===Noun===
'''gūþ''' (''pl'' '''gūþa''')
# [[battle]], [[combat]]
#:''Ic geneþde fela guþa'': I dared many battles.  (''Beowulf'')

